data.chText: 尽显其宏伟气象的兰斯大教堂景色
data.enText: a view of Rheims Cathedral, in all its splendour

data.chText: 宫殿经过修葺，重现出昔日的富丽堂皇。
data.enText: The palace has been restored to its former splendour.

data.chText: （尤指某地的）壮丽景色，恢弘气势
data.enText: the beautiful and impressive features or qualities of sth, especially a place
the splendours of Rome (= its fine buildings, etc.)

means: (尤指某地的)壮丽景色，恢弘气势

tr: the quality of being magnificent or splendid or grand
example: for magnificence and personal service there is the Queen's hotel
his `Hamlet' lacks the brilliance that one expects
it is the university that gives the scene its stately splendor
an imaginative mix of old-fashioned grandeur and colorful art
advertisers capitalize on the grandness and elegance it brings to their products

tr: a quality that outshines the usual

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 splendor

value.def: The splendour of something is its beautiful and impressive appearance.

example.ex: The foreign ministers are meeting in the splendour of Oktyabrskaya Hotel in central Moscow.
example.tran: 外长们正在莫斯科市中心富丽堂皇的十月酒店里开会。

value.def: The splendours of a place or way of life are its beautiful and impressive features.

example.ex: Montagu was extremely impressed by the splendours of the French court.
example.tran: 法国宫廷的豪华给蒙塔古留下了很深的印象。
